snippet: President Asif Ali Zardari of Pakistan is ending his term in office, becoming the first democratically elected president in the country’s history to complete his full tenure.
abstract: Outgoing Pakistani Pres Asif Ali Zardari will become first democratically elected president in country's history to complete his full tenure; Zardari fended off threat after threat over his five years in power, confounding expectations.

byline.contributor: Salman Masood contributed reporting from Islamabad, Pakistan.

lead_paragraph: President Asif Ali Zardari of Pakistan is ending his term in office, becoming the first democratically elected president in the country’s history to complete his full tenure.

headline.main: Making History in Pakistan Simply by Serving a Full Term
headline.print_headline: Making History in Pakistan Simply by Serving a Full Term
